column5: It was tough sledding but 4 of us went out yesterday.  Lots of perch with steady action all day except for one 10 minute lull-we never had to move. Fish were hitting on minnows, small jigging spoons and jigging raps; I kept a dozen decent ones for dinner.
Nice.  Seems perch are abundent on Simcoe for all to enjoy.
Nice little haul man, cant say the same for us yeaterday...no keepers.
